    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-06-16T05:35:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-06-16T05:35:00-05:00" n="329"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d329">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">811.20(D)Regulations/2781: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Iran</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Moose</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tehran</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-06-16T14:00:00+03:25"
                            >June 16, 1941—2 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received June 16—1:35 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>59. The Acting Minister of Foreign Affairs requests that the Department assist in
                    obtaining export permit for aluminum valued at about 7,000 pounds sterling and
                    110 tons of copper tubing which he states are intended solely for the Iranian
                    Army and not for sale nor re-export.</p>
                <p>The Iranian Minister in Washington is being instructed to pursue the request and
                    to supply details.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Moose</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
